                    "Two units of prayer by the learned weigh over seventy units by laymen. ~ Prophet Mohammad (s.a.w)",
                    "Two things are penalized by God in this world tyranny and ungratefulness to parents. ~ Prophet Mohammad (s.a.w)",
                    "Two things are amazing a silly mans wise sayings, which you have to welcome, and a wise mans bad words which you should ignore- Muhammad ~ Prophet Mohammad (s.a.w)",
                    "Two hungry wolves in a sheepfold are less dangerous to the sheep than ambition for position and wealth to a Muslims faith. ~ Prophet Mohammad (s.a.w)",
                    "Two hungry persons will never be satiated the seeker of knowledge and the seeker of wealth. ~ Prophet Mohammad (s.a.w)",
                    "Two characteristics do not dwell in a believer avarice and ill temper. ~ Prophet Mohammad (s.a.w)",
                    "Two brothers are like unto two hands, one bathing the other. ~ Prophet Mohammad (s.a.w)",
                    "Two real friends enjoy each others company. ~ Prophet Mohammad (s.a.w)",
                    "Try to be kind, for a kind person wants people to be at good and in abundance. ~ Prophet Mohammad (s.a.w)",
                    "Truthfulness is peace lying is anxiety. ~ Prophet Mohammad (s.a.w)",
                    "Truth of the tongue leads to truth of the heart and that, in turn, leads to truth of ones faith. ~ Prophet Mohammad (s.a.w)",
