                    "God has made wine and all the intoxicant unlawful. ~ Prophet Mohammad (s.a.w)",
                    "God has forbidden Paradise for the scurrilous people who dont care about what they say and hear. ~ Prophet Mohammad (s.a.w)",
                    "God has decreed this nation Muslims to suffer their punishment in this very world. ~ Prophet Mohammad (s.a.w)",
                    "God has created something to overcome any other created thing, and thus, His Mercy has He created to overcome His anger. ~ Prophet Mohammad (s.a.w)",
                    "God has commanded me to behave moderately with people, as he has commanded me to perform my obligations. ~ Prophet Mohammad (s.a.w)",
                    "God grants a good friend to the one for whom He wishes good. ~ Prophet Mohammad (s.a.w)",
                    "God gives sustenance to the frugal and deprives it from the extravagant. ~ Prophet Mohammad (s.a.w)",
                    "God gives chastity and abundance to the one who seeks them. ~ Prophet Mohammad (s.a.w)",
                    "God does not trust in hypocrites. ~ Prophet Mohammad (s.a.w)",
                    "God does not observe a heretics deeds unless heabandons his her heresy. ~ Prophet Mohammad (s.a.w)",
                    "God does not forgive the killer of a believer, and accepts not his her repentance. ~ Prophet Mohammad (s.a.w)",
                    "God does not endear the ignorant, nor does He degrade the patient. ~ Prophet Mohammad (s.a.w)",
                    "God created the creatures and determined their fates, deeds, and sustenance. ~ Prophet Mohammad (s.a.w)",
                    "Gluttony hardens mans heart. ~ Prophet Mohammad (s.a.w)",
                    "Glorify whats divine, and Gods glory will be thine. ~ Prophet Mohammad (s.a.w)",
                    "Glorify God to be forgiven by Him. ~ Prophet Mohammad (s.a.w)",
                    "Giving charity is the best path to piety. ~ Prophet Mohammad (s.a.w)",
                    "Giving charity early in morning takes away all evils. ~ Prophet Mohammad (s.a.w)",
                    "Giving alms to kins is alms giving as well as strengthening ties of kinship. ~ Prophet Mohammad (s.a.w)",
                    "Givers and receivers of bribe are both subject to the fire of Hell. ~ Prophet Mohammad (s.a.w)",
                    "Give up the doubtful and grasp the undoubtful Verily, truthfulness entails salvation. ~ Prophet Mohammad (s.a.w)",
                    "Give up hope for what people have and avoid avarice, for it is immediate poverty. ~ Prophet Mohammad (s.a.w)",
                    "Give something to a beggar, even if it is half a date petty. ~ Prophet Mohammad (s.a.w)",
