                    "Get accustomed to grief, for its the light of mans heart Keep yourself hungry and thirsty. ~ Prophet Mohammad (s.a.w)",
                    "Generosity is Gods outstanding attribute. ~ Prophet Mohammad (s.a.w)",
                    "Friendship and enmity are both hereditary. ~ Prophet Mohammad (s.a.w)",
                    "Frequent people time and again, more beloved to remain. ~ Prophet Mohammad (s.a.w)",
                    "Four things show ones wretchedness drained eyes, hard  heartedness, inaccessible ambitions and excessive love for survival. ~ Prophet Mohammad (s.a.w)",
                    "Four things ruin a house, should its residents act upon them treachery, theft, drinking wine and adultery. ~ Prophet Mohammad (s.a.w)",
                    "Four things have been predestined for Adams son his physical appearance, character, death, and sustenance. ~ Prophet Mohammad (s.a.w)",
                    "Foul mouthedness, debauchery and stinginess suffice to make of man a sinner. ~ Prophet Mohammad (s.a.w)",
                    "Forgiving is the best of all deeds. ~ Prophet Mohammad (s.a.w)",
                    "Forgive punishable sins among yourselves for punishment will be inevitable should you make me aware of them. ~ Prophet Mohammad (s.a.w)",
                    "Forgive each other to make your grudges drop. ~ Prophet Mohammad (s.a.w)",
                    "Forgetfulness ruins knowledge, and the knowledge transmitted to incompetent people will be ruined too. ~ Prophet Mohammad (s.a.w)",
                    "For others health always pray, and you will enjoy it without delay. ~ Prophet Mohammad (s.a.w)",
                    "For his faults, a generous man, do not reprimand, for whenever he slips, God gives him a helping hand. ~ Prophet Mohammad (s.a.w)",
                    "For everything there is a key, and the key to skies is saying, There is no god but Allah. ~ Prophet Mohammad (s.a.w)",
                    "For everything there is a key, and the key to Paradise is to love the poor and the needy. ~ Prophet Mohammad (s.a.w)",
                    "For everything there is a beauty, and for the Quran, a nice recitation. ~ Prophet Mohammad (s.a.w)",
                    "For everything there is a form of harm leading to its ruin, and the harm to this religion are corrupt rulers. ~ Prophet Mohammad (s.a.w)",
                    "For everything some alms are due, and for the body, fasting. ~ Prophet Mohammad (s.a.w)",
                    "For everything some alms are due, and for ones house, the drawing room. ~ Prophet Mohammad (s.a.w)",
                    "For every sin there is a form of penitence, save for bad temperedness. ~ Prophet Mohammad (s.a.w)",
                    "For every disease, God has devised a certain remedy. ~ Prophet Mohammad (s.a.w)",
